removeEmpty

public void removeEmpty()
Description copied from interface: JsonElement
Removes empty elements from a json tree. An object is empty if it contains no elements or if all the entries in it are empty. Likewise a list is empty if it has no elements or only empty elements. Finally, primitives are considered empty if the value is null or if the string value is equal to "".

Specified by:
removeEmpty in interface JsonElement
